                            <comment id="17551993" author="mgrigorov" created="Thu, 9 Jun 2022 07:08:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Wow! I didn&apos;t expect that String.format() would do such things!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now I see that there is java.lang.String#format(java.util.Locale, java.lang.String, java.lang.Object...)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=solomax&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;solomax&quot;&gt;solomax&lt;/a&gt; Did you check whether there are more usages of String.format() with %d in the rest of Wicket ? If there are then we should either rework them to string concatenation like here or provide Locale.ROOT as first argument.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17552022" author="solomax" created="Thu, 9 Jun 2022 07:51:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mgrigorov&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mgrigorov&quot;&gt;mgrigorov&lt;/a&gt; I&apos;ve greped by &lt;tt&gt;%d&lt;/tt&gt; and found no other suspects&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I thought to use &lt;tt&gt;String#format(java.util.Locale, java.lang.String, java.lang.Object...)&lt;/tt&gt; but this might do unexpected transform to ROOT locale of it&apos;s params &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/sad.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
